## Backend API

Base URL: `http://localhost:8080`

- `GET /healthz`
- `GET /api/v1/cameras?start=0&length=25`
  - Calls 511NY's camera JSON endpoint with browser-like headers + session priming.
- `GET /api/v1/cameras/recommended?count=5`
  - Returns top camera candidates (default 5; supports 1-10) for your MVP corridor focus.
- `POST /api/v1/pipeline/start?camera_count=5`
  - Starts the in-memory focus pipeline selection (invalid values default to 5; valid range 5-10).
- `GET /api/v1/pipeline/focus/stream?mode=live|processed`
  - Returns focus snapshot stream bytes for `<img>` usage (`mode=raw` is treated as `processed`).
- `POST /api/v1/pipeline/focus/detect?stream_id=cam-49&imgsz=640&conf=0.25`
  - Fetches current focus snapshot and forwards bytes to detector sidecar (`DETECTOR_BASE_URL/internal/detect`).
  - Supports passthrough MOT/ROI params (`iou`, `roi`, `lanes`, `direction`, `moving_speed_threshold_px_s`, `smoothing_window_sec`, `debug_overlay`).
  - Returns workflow state (`running`/`cooldown`/`ready`) to prevent detector request floods.
- `GET /api/v1/analysis/plan`
  - Returns baseline latency/model/alert strategy.
- `POST /api/v1/pipeline/start`
  - Starts rolling-buffer incident pipeline.
- `POST /api/v1/pipeline/stop`
  - Stops the pipeline.
- `GET /api/v1/pipeline/status`
  - Running state, camera count, uptime, config summary.
- `GET /api/v1/pipeline/cameras`
  - Live per-camera processing view (raw + processed frame URLs + metrics).
- `GET /api/v1/pipeline/focus/stream?camera_id=...&mode=processed|raw&fps=30`
  - MJPEG focus stream for near-real-time browser viewing (target up to 30fps).
- `POST /api/v1/pipeline/focus/detect?camera_id=...`
  - Proxies image bytes to YOLO sidecar (`/internal/detect`) for focused-view overlay boxes + object metrics.
  - Includes lane geometry (`geometry.lanes`) when provided by detector config/query, enabling polygon lane overlays in focused view.
- `GET /api/v1/alerts?limit=100`
  - Structured incident alerts with evidence links.
- `GET /artifacts/*`
  - Serves saved before/after snapshots and event GIF clips.

### Run backend

```bash
cd backend
go run ./cmd/api
```

Environment variables:

- `PORT` (default `8080`)
- `NY511_BASE_URL` (default `https://511ny.org`)
- `DETECTOR_BASE_URL` (default `http://localhost:8090`)

